reviews_data.review_text: Terrible customer service, cashier was not friendly…ordered shaved ice and cashier had an attitude.  Also many flies all over the bread/pastries in the case. Won’t be coming back to this location.

It would be nice to be able to use a changing table since I was trying to change my baby's diaper during my visit. If there was a changing table in the toilet I would give a 5 star

It was a very nice place I loved the decoration and the food here is so good, my favorite was strawberry croissants, and the people were so nice telling us what they liked or what they digested to get over all it was a very nice place to go.

The food is decent, the prices are a little high, but the service is absolutely horrendous. I live in very close proximity to this location and I’ve been in there twice to just grab a coffee and literally wait 5 to 10 minutes before anyone speaks to you. I like to try and support smaller businesses, but not when service is that bad
I love this place😍
best binsoo 沙冰 in Charlotte!
Ordered their mango cloud cake for celebrating milestone birthday and it was epic! Can’t wait to have more. They are so picture perfect and equally delicious!

Me and my friend came here today around 12pm and the staff that were working were absolutely amazing! I regret not having to remember the names but the were so kind and helpful! Each member went above and beyond expectations! Will be coming back!
A wonderful French bakery. So many choices. All good.
Very nice bakery, good sweet items, savory stuff is decent but I prefer the sweet items from their menu!! Overall great service and tables are clean!

Relaxing environment very kind employees, FOOD IS AMAZING try the cheese mochi, i recommend getting there early for everything to come out toasty n fresh but it truly is delicious everything is!!! AND ITS AFFORDABLE
I love iced matcha latte here 🤤 everything is so tasty 😋

I love coming to this place. All of their pastries are always up to standard and amazing! My favorite savory pastry is the kimchi croquette, and my favorite sweet is the chocolate croissant or the mango croissant! Today I tried the mango croissant and the matcha tiramisu latte with oat milk! The mango croissant was great, I loved that the croissant was fully filled with the mango cream. I’ve had their original matcha latte with oat milk and it was alright. I definitely liked the tiramisu matcha better even though it is on the sweeter side. Wish they offered soy milk!! Overall great place! :D
The desserts are amazing!

Cute spot, definitely more Asian than French. 5 for creativity and originality. Really good pastry combos. The coffee quality was a good maybe not the syrups. The pasties don’t taste as fresh, not stale either.. more like premade a day prior. The place tends to be crowded and limited indoor seating some outdoor seating also. Would only return if meeting up with friends like it or would want to try, but nothing I would drive out the way for. South Charlotte bakery, vegetarian options, ample parking

Pretty good! I tried a cheesecake for the first time and it was good. I loved what there was to offer and I really want to try some other selections of goodies next time. Also the cashier was very polite in her service. 👍🏼
Great food
Best bakery in Ballantyne.. cloud cakes, crossiants tiramisu tubs everything is super yummy.. don’t miss just visit

The food was good but the matcha tiramisu was TO DIE FORRRRR
It literally was so good.
Not as amazing as presented on Instagram.
Someone tell them how to provide a good service. The staff is rude. And they dont know-how to make effin coffee. Not once..not twice but has happened many times.

Ive always loved this chain. The food is really good as always. The place has good energy. But the service is very poor especially the coffee making skills. The coffee is always bad at this location. It always feel like they are happy with just serving the food but not make good coffees. Some of the people who work here are gonna let this place down

I used to love coming here, the food & coffee is amazing. But today I came in and ordered a cold brew latte, and I’ve got this drink many times before at the other locations too, and when they handed it to me it looked like cold brew with the tiniest splash of milk. I saw that the person who made it was training because he was asking a lot of questions, so I asked if it was supposed to be that color, because I had ordered it so many times before and it was always milky, as a latte should be. The girl behind the counter explained that’s what it was, and told me I was confused and probably meant to order a regular latte. Even though I explained I’ve been ordering that from Tous and it never looked like that before. I’m an ex barista, I know the difference between cold brew and espresso and a latte versus just a splash of milk, but she made me feel too embarrassed to keep explaining so I just asked if I could have a regular latte in its place. When she handed me the new drink she looked annoyed and didn’t say anything.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello. Lauren.
I’m sorry for your bad experience.There must have been a problem in the process of training new employees. From now on ,I will work hard on employee training and provide better service.Thank you.

reviews_data.review_text: So fun! So many yummy options to choose from. Lots of variety and interesting breads. It s a unique but simple experience. Would be fun to take friends / out of town visitors too and is great when you need to bring something to a party.

The food here is ✨️DELICIOUS✨️!! I wish I could go everyday... so I buy extra for eating during the week 😍 I love how they package the pastries individually, it's extremely helpful! Plus all the different types of pastries you wouldn't find at our regular grocery stores.
Also if you eat there, you can ask them to heat up your food you'd like to eat there! It's very admirable even when they are busy... (which they almost always are!)
There's also a nice seating area outside for beautiful days🌻🧁🍰
Delicious foods with diverse flavors, and comfortable ☺️ it's a must try!
Always a pleasure

Great pastries and baked goods options with somewhat reasonable pricing.  Coffees have been good, but not really memorable.  Service could be a little better, friendlier overall and that's based on the few times I've been here.  Clean, well kept environment.  Only a few tables inside with additional outdoor seating and a good size patio space.
We had a great experience with the amazing coffee and bakery for breakfast. The food quality is amazing and the coffee tastes great, hitting the right flavors and aroma. I'll go again and again.

Tous les Jours is amazing!
Their coffee is wonderful and the pastries are fresh, tasty and unique!
The staff have all been pleasant and helpful and it’s so clean and inviting!
They have set up the outdoor patio real cute too!!
Such a wonderful selection of treats!
I’m so excited my favorite bakery is here. My kids got my 50th bday cake and it was the best

I recently visited yesterday to pick up a birthday cake for myself, and while I’ve had good experiences here before, this visit was disappointing. Upon entering, I was greeted warmly by one of the employees, but another staff member with glasses had a noticeably bad attitude.

I initially spoke with the friendly employee about the cakes, and once I made my decision, I let her know. However, the other employee suddenly chimed in with an unnecessary attitude, questioning whether I wanted the whole cake or just a slice—even though I was already being helped. It was confusing and made the interaction uncomfortable.

When it was time to pay, the unfriendly employee was the one who rang me up. I asked her to apply my military discount, as I’ve always received it at this café before. She immediately dismissed it, claiming they don’t offer one. Since I knew otherwise, she had to check with the manager, who confirmed the discount was valid. Instead of simply applying it, she then sarcastically asked for my military ID in a way that insinuated I was lying, which I found extremely disrespectful.

I remained polite and provided my ID, but this entire experience left a bad taste in my mouth. As a loyal customer, I expect to be treated with basic courtesy, not skepticism and attitude. I hope management takes this into account because unwelcoming service like this can easily drive customers away.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello. Krystal.
I am so sorry for the bad experience for you.There’s a lot to pay attention to we just opened up.I will pay more attention to the customer service. Thank you.

reviews_data.review_text: This place is a “have to go”!! Everything it’s incredible !

I was really excited to try this bakery, but unfortunately, the experience was disappointing. The pastries were decent, but the customer service was awful. The girl at the register was extremely rude - she acted like I was bothering her just by placing an order and was very short with me the entire time. A good bakery isn’t just about the food, it’s also about the atmosphere and service, and this place definitely needs to improve in that area. I won’t be coming back.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello, Leyla.
I am so sorry for the bad experience for you.I don’t think we’ve been able to provide you with the best service since we just opened.I will pay more attention from now on. Thank you.
